Picture: AllanGray.co.za The move follows the agency reluctantly leaving King James in 2014 after the Cape-based agency won the Sanlam account, so Ogilvy had a hard act to follow. &#x201c;I can confirm that we have ended our agency relationship with Ogilvy Cape Town, and have awarded the account to another agency,&#x201d; Henk Pieterse, head of marketing at Allan Gray, told Marklives. Other than that, &#x201c;both parties are mum about why the relationship broke down&#x201d;, reported Financial Mail.